The paper deals with a communication problem involving the exchange of data packets among users, which is a classic topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The problem involves dividing users into sub-groups, which suggests a possible connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of linear programming and the analysis of random packet distribution suggest a possible connection to optimization (cs.LG).
